Computer Language: (("Lehrsprachen" "How to Design Programs" "AnfÃ¤nger") (#(#t constructor repeating-decimal #f #t none) #f ((lib "image.ss" "teachpack" "2htdp") (lib "universe.ss" "teachpack" "2htdp"))))
>Description:
The grammars of the *SL languages contain the following production for expressions:

 expr = ...
  | (and expr expr expr ...)
  | (or expr expr expr ...)

The correct grammar should be

 expr = ...
  | (and expr expr ...)
  | (or expr expr ...)
>How-To-Repeat:
>Fix:
>Audit-Trail:
